    Scanner scanner = new Scanner ( path , StandardCharsets.UTF_8 ) ;

A `Scanner` is a resource that should be closed when no longer needed. As a habit, use the [try-with-resources][3] syntax to automatically close. And catch any `IOException`. 

Within our try-with-resources, parse the file.

Specify the delimiter. For our needs that means a newline, to parse each line. 

    scanner.useDelimiter ( &quot;\n&quot; );

For each line, split the string into our two parts. 

