We use each part to instantiate an object our of our class `Airline` which we defined as a [record][4]. 

    record Airline( String name , Year founded ) { }

We add each new `Airline` object to a list. And finally dump that list to the console.

We loop the lines by leveraging the fact that a [`Scanner`][5] is an [`Iterator`][6]. An `Iterator` has a [`forEachRemaining`][7] method to make the looping neat. We pass a lambda to handle each line. If you are not comfortable with lambdas yet, you can replace the `forEachRemaining` with a conventional loop.

